Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN)  appointed Rob Jesudason as head of a new global emerging markets team within
the financial institutions group, according to an internal memo
obtained by Bloomberg News.  Jesudason, previously head of financial institutions in
Asia Pacific, will be responsible for coverage teams across the
Asia-Pacific region, Central and Eastern Europe, Middle East,
Africa and Latin America, the memo said.  Credit Suisse also appointed Simon Yuan and Nicolo Salsano
as co-heads of the Asia-Pacific financial institutions group.
They will report to Jesudason, who will remain based in  Hong
Kong , according to the memo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
